        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 1. Polyonyx similis, new species. A, B, D–H, holotype, male (cl 5.0 mm), stn B24, NMCR 27071; C, I, J, paratype, ovigerous female (cl 5.5 mm), stn B24, NMCR 27072. A, carapace and ocular and antennal peduncles, dorsal view; B, C, rostrum, anterior view; D, third and forth thoracic sternites, ventral view; E, telson, external view; F, basal segment of left antennular peduncle, ventral view; G, right anterior part of carapace and ocular and antennal peduncles, anterolateral view; H, left third maxilliped, lateral view (long setae on ventral margin omitted); I, J, left fifth pereopod, chela and distal part of carpus, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." ;
